latestPosts.caption:
Tall enough to kiss the stars. Soft enough to guard a dream. 

Meet The Chromatic Beasts, a collectible statement sculpture series where surrealism meets safari in a hyper-contemporary chrome skin. These towering giraffes are more than décor; they’re emotional architecture. Crafted for expansive luxury interiors, they command presence, soften space, and spark conversation.

Finished in iridescent hues of emerald, gold, and oceanic blues, each dot is intentional, merging nature’s whimsy with pop-art precision. Ideal for high-ceiling foyers, atriums, and gallery-style homes, the work blurs the line between installation and investment. This is art for the collector who dares to be unforgettable.

@taoartgallery x @jayeshsachdev

latestPosts.caption:
“Air of Majesty” The sculpture is a radiant portrayal of strength and celebration, crafted in the form of a majestic elephant, symbolising power and grace. The inflated balloon-like design transforms the otherwise colossal and heavy essence of the elephant into an object of lightness and joy, embodying the paradox of balance—where might meets playfulness. 12” H x 16” L x 5.5” D

Find it on @thehouseofthings x @jayeshsachdev and @taoartgalleryonline

latestPosts.caption:
Jayesh x Zara wasn’t just India’s first-ever artist collaboration with @zara that was about Fashion alone, it was a full-blown art movement, that involved Merchandise, Packaging Design, Visual Merchandise, and a massive Sculpture. From artworks and illustrations to a 10-foot sculpture built over three months this was more than fashion, it was a creative statement.

That very sculpture, once launched at the Zara Palladium store in Mumbai, now all Thanks to Zara’ and @mish.star.gram persistent efforts, stands gloriously at the Nita Mukesh Ambani Cultural Centre @nmacc.india in Mumbai, one of India’s most prestigious art spaces.

If you’re at NMACC, find it. Take a photo. Tag me. Let’s celebrate this surreal moment together.

#ZaraXJayesh #NMACC #Sculpture #PublicArt #ContemporaryArt #JayeshSachdev #ArtCollab #zaraxjayeshsachdev #InstallationArt

A delirious sugar rush sculpted in form, this series is a candy-coated daydream, bursting with the energy of tropical sweets and neon indulgence. Imagine bubblegum rebellion drizzled in coconut milk, whipped into a psychedelic parfait of pop and play.

Extending my love for Balloons, Candy and Colour all indulged into one scoop as Installation Art pieces, sculpted in Fibre Glass and Automotive Paint.
